<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="How Cat Gear Index researches, structures, updates, and discloses cat supply recommendations.">
  <article class="article-shell">
    <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">We prioritize verifiable product data, clear limitations, and practical ownership costs.</p>
    <h2>Research Standards</h2>
    <p>Product records should cite official specifications, approved retailer details, owner feedback patterns, and hands-on testing where available. Sample records are not recommendations.</p>
    <h2>Review Updates</h2>
    <p>Every product record includes an update date. High-change categories such as automatic litter boxes, filters, recalls, and replacement parts should be reviewed frequently.</p>
    <h2>Medical Boundary</h2>
    <p>We do not diagnose pets, recommend medical treatment, or make veterinary claims. Health-related product claims must be attributed to reliable sources and handled conservatively.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
